FBIS4-60099 "drnes098_k_94001" FBIS-NES-94-098 Daily Report 19 May 1994 IRAQ Kurdish Islamic Movement Reports Clashes With PUK Kurdish Islamic Movement Reports Clashes With PUK NC1905190494 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran in Arabic 1730 GMT 19 May 94 NC1905190494 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran Arabic BFN [Text] A spokesman for the Islamic Movement in Iraqi Kurdistan has announced that his movement carried out military operations yesterday, during which it regained Tappah Kurrah, (Muhammad Abad), (Kumalar), Anab, Bakrawah, Sirah, and Halabjah from the forces of the Patriot Union of Kurdistan [PUK], at the same time killing a number of PUK troops. The spokesman added that the Islamic Movement is continuing its advance and is besieging the city of Sayyid Sadiq. He added that during their occupation of the above-mentioned villages, Jalal Talabani's forces violated people's honor, carried out murders and massacres, and stole livestock. The Islamic Movement spokesman said that the citizens of Shanaderi Khwaru fled to the plains and wadis to escape the PUK forces' assaults.
